# CIRO Mobile App - Part 2 Implementation

## Summary of Changes
Implemented the mobile UI shell and state management logic as defined in the agent prompt for Part 2 of the CIRO app.

### State Management
- **`store/crisisStore.ts`**: Created a Zustand store to handle agent states, logs, and simulation output, mirroring the backend structures.

### UI Components
- **`components/AgentCard.tsx`**: A dynamic component rendering individual agent details with state-based animated borders, streaming log outputs, and collapsible JSON result sections.
- **`components/LogEntry.tsx`**: A component designed to map `executionLogs` to readable lines with icons matching severity.

### Screens & Routing
- **`app/_layout.tsx`**: Global stack layout with dark theme configurations.
- **`app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`**: Bottom tab navigation setup to route between Home, Agents, Map, Actions, Alerts, and Logs.
- **`app/(tabs)/index.tsx`**: The main Home screen. Implemented the reporting UI, Live Crisis list, Signal Feed placeholders, and integrated the complete `runDemoSequence` and `runFalseAlarmDemo` functions.
- **`app/(tabs)/agents.tsx`**: The Agent Activity screen. Created the full flow of interconnected `AgentCard` components and appended the "Baseline Comparison" UI at the bottom.

## Validation Results
We successfully typed all data models. Please start your Expo project (`npx expo start`) and test the app in Expo Go on your physical device. Make sure to press the "Run Demo" buttons to see the backend interactions and agent card animations running live!

> [!TIP]
> Ensure your `BASE_URL` in `constants/config.ts` matches your current Local IP exactly before testing the backend integration.
